            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Warning to future readers:&lt;/b&gt; This answer inaccurately applies the term &lt;i&gt;Currying&lt;/i&gt;. &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/a/36321/4639281&quot;&gt;&lt;i&gt;&quot;Currying is when you break down a function that takes multiple arguments into a series of functions that take part of the arguments.&quot;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. This code does nothing of the sort. All you&apos;ve done here is take the code from the accepted answer, move some things around, change the style and naming a bit, then call it currying, which it categorically is not.&lt;/span&gt;

